liquid.engine

Class LiquidEngine

  • java.lang.Object
    • liquid.engine.LiquidEngine
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable, Interfaceable

    public class LiquidEngine
extends java.lang.Object
implements Interfaceable, java.lang.Runnable
    LiquidEngine is the central class of the Engine, where all components have been derived from the jBox2D software. Here, all GUI objects are implemented and taken effect and all particle/velocity data values are calculated and stored.

    This class also interfaces between the GUI and Logger to pass particle/velocity information.

    • Method Detail

      • send

        public void send(Interfaceable i,
                 GlobalVar.Request request)
        Method defines requested interactions to the GUI and Logger.

        Current Send Interactions:
        - REQUEST_DISPLAY_SIM - sends the GUI a request to display current particle data
        - REQUEST_PRINT_SIM - sends the GUI a request to display current flow meter/breakpoint data
        - REQUEST_SIM_HAS_ENDED - sends the GUI a notice that the runtime specified has been reached

        - REQUEST_WRITE_LOG_DATA - sends the Logger a request to write current flow meter/breakpoint data

        Specified by:
        send in interface Interfaceable
        Parameters:
        i - - determines which component to request an interaction with
        request - - determines what interaction to request

      • receive

        public void receive(Interfaceable i,
                    GlobalVar.Request request,
                    java.lang.String[] args)
        Method defines requested interactions from the GUI and Logger.

        Current Receive Interactions:
        - RUN_SIM - receives a notice from the GUI to run the simulation
        - PAUSE_SIM - receives a notice from the GUI to pause the simulation
        - STEP_SIM - receives a notice from the GUI to proceed showing 1 frame of the simulation
        - END_SIM - receives a notice from the GUI to end the simulation

        Specified by:
        receive in interface Interfaceable
        Parameters:
        i - - determines which component is requesting an interaction
        request - - determines what interaction is requested
        args - - information required to complete requested interaction

      • initSim

        public void initSim(java.lang.String[] args)
        Method establishes the simulation environment using parameters passed through args.
        Parameters:
        args - - array holding all object parameters for current simulation, generated by LiquidGUI

      • run

        public void run()
        Method runs the simulation, the time period dependent on the specified runtime in the GUI. The Frames Per Second (FPS) have also been calculated, mainly used as a debugging tool to determine the performance of the running simulation. This is appreciated for testing with many many particles.
        Specified by:
        run in interface java.lang.Runnable

      • dispose

        public void dispose()
        Method disposes of the Engine when the application has stopped.
